                            <comment id="12716169" author="emtrane" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2009 07:15:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, Noble. Does this mean any nightly build after 5/20 has your patch applied to it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775736" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:52:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14088263" author="archanak" created="Wed, 6 Aug 2014 22:11:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;We are facing a similar issue but out use case is nested entity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we have the below nested entitties&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ParentEntity&lt;br/&gt;
    chilld1Entity&lt;br/&gt;
         child2Entity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;child1Entity is child of ParentEntity and parent of child2Entity. Child2Entity is child of child1Entity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when we add deltaImportQuery on child2Entity. It is not executing deltaImportQuery during delta import.&lt;br/&gt;
I found that below code(#503) in the DocBuilder class is restricting the deltaImportQuery from not being executed at the nested child entity level.&lt;br/&gt;
for (EntityProcessorWrapper child : epw.getChildren()) &lt;/p&gt;
{
              buildDocument(vr, doc,
                  child.getEntity().isDocRoot() ? pk : null, child, false, ctx, entitiesToDestroy);
            }</comment>
